<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="370" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,880,1123]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,953,979]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Remarks</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[323,442,952,979]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1759,1783]" captionTargetBox="[278,1330,215,1685]" captionTargetId="figure-33@6.[244,1344,181,1735]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 3A–C. A. Abdomen of male Zavrelimyia (Paramerina) valida (Paul, Mazumdar and Hazra, 2013); B. Hypopygium of male Zavrelimyia (Paramerina) valida (Paul, Mazumdar and Hazra, 2013); C. Hypopygium of male Zavrelimyia (Schineriella) schineri (Strobl, 1880). Both to scale: 50 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6644854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6644854/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Figure 3C</figureCitation>
). The specimen examined has AR 1.9, no R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[936,961,971,985]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">2+3</subScript>
vein, mid and hind legs each with 2 tibial spurs, LR 
<subScript attach="left" box="[260,268,1007,1021]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">1</subScript>
0.89, a hind tibial comb with 6 setae and fully conforms with that of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Strobl)" baseAuthorityName="Strobl" baseAuthorityYear="1880" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Zavrelimyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schineri" subGenus="Schineriella">
<emphasis box="[1044,1178,988,1014]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Zavrelimyia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1194,1329,988,1014]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Schineriella</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1346,1436,988,1014]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">schineri</emphasis>
(Strobl)
</taxonomicName>
in morphometry and hypopygium structures.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="370" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,880,1123]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1060,1086]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Distribution</emphasis>
: Previously, the species was reported from the Palaearctic region (
<bibRefCitation author="Ashe, P. &amp; O'Connor, J. P." box="[1096,1374,1060,1087]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" refId="ref12310" refString="Ashe, P. &amp; O'Connor, J. P. (2009) A World Catalogue of Chironomidae (Diptera). Part 1. Buchonomyiinae, Chilenomyiinae, Podonominae, Aphroteniinae, Tanypodinae, Usambaromyiinae, Diamesinae, Prodiamesinae and Telmatogetoninae. Irish Biogeographical Society and National Museum of Ireland, Dublin, 445 pp." type="book" year="2009">Ashe &amp; O’Connor 2009</bibRefCitation>
). The record from 
<collectingCountry box="[291,349,1096,1122]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">India</collectingCountry>
shows the distribution of this species as extending to the Oriental region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
